            <h3 class="subheading">Cubby Hole Founder and Entrepreneur</h3>
            <p> As an 8 year old child, Lee built kits, and it has been a lifelong love ever since, when time and tide allowed. 
              Currently a head chef at a busy restaurant in a quaint pub that dick Turpin used to visit, he now spends all his days off in the Cubby “tinkering” as he puts it. 
              This being usually on 1:48 scale prop driven WW2 aircraft or jets from the Falklands war. 
              </p><p>Lee decided to found the Cubby when modelling helped him get through severe illness and cognitive impairment. He is a keen advocate of what the modelling hobby and community can do to help people overcome personal barriers and help develop healthy mindfulness. 
              He currently lives in Bridlington with his wife, three children and dog “Ollie the Wally”.</p>
